Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and document representation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new method for document encoding using Tree-LSTMs. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses document classification and improving performance in this task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a new method for encoding documents that could be applied in various AI applications. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions visualizing attention inside a document, which could be related to visualizing attention in image processing tasks.
